The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Sachs award likely on Thursday

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Late on Monday, the International Cricket Council indicated that arbiter Justice Albie Sachs may make his award on the Sourav Ganguly issue known on Thursday, according to information reaching here. 

Justice Sachs award will have an impact on Souravs six-ODI ban. If it is favourable, Sourav will head for Sri Lanka as the 16th player for the tri-series. Otherwise, he will have to miss the tournament. 

The tri-series starts on Saturday with India taking on hosts Sri Lanka in the opener in Dambulla under lights. The final is on August 9. 




